839
00:39:41,679 --> 00:39:43,119
I gave her thirty.

840
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:46,079
She wouldn't give me change.

841
00:39:46,800 --> 00:39:48,239
She insisted I was dirty.

842
00:39:48,239 --> 00:39:49,519
She wanted five more.

843
00:39:50,440 --> 00:39:51,599
That made me really angry.

844
00:39:52,000 --> 00:39:53,880
So I did it to her.

845
00:39:54,199 --> 00:39:56,840
You killed her over five bucks?

846
00:40:00,400 --> 00:40:01,840
I didn't mean to kill her.

847
00:40:02,519 --> 00:40:03,880
She kept cursing at me.

848
00:40:05,000 --> 00:40:06,800
I hit her with a brick.

849
00:40:07,280 --> 00:40:08,159
She kept cursing.

850
00:40:08,599 --> 00:40:10,960
Not just cursing, she slapped me too.

851
00:40:11,039 --> 00:40:12,480
She slapped you, so you killed her?

852
00:40:13,559 --> 00:40:15,239
Your foreman slapped you too.

853
00:40:15,239 --> 00:40:16,519
Are you going to kill him as well?

854
00:40:17,920 --> 00:40:19,920
A slap I could let go.

855
00:40:20,480 --> 00:40:22,199
But her insults got worse and worse.

856
00:40:22,679 --> 00:40:24,400
She even cursed that I'd never have children.

857
00:40:25,719 --> 00:40:26,440
And then?

858
00:40:28,719 --> 00:40:31,400
I saw a fruit knife nearby.

859
00:40:31,840 --> 00:40:34,760
I picked it up and stabbed her.

860
00:40:35,880 --> 00:40:36,559
Where's the knife?

861
00:40:37,440 --> 00:40:38,800
I threw it in the trash pile.

862
00:40:38,840 --> 00:40:40,079
How far did you go to throw it away?

863
00:40:40,719 --> 00:40:42,320
Was it a garbage pile or a trash can?

864
00:40:42,960 --> 00:40:44,159
It could have been a can.

865
00:40:44,840 --> 00:40:46,079
I don't remember.

866
00:40:54,360 --> 00:40:55,159
Brother Dali

867
00:40:56,440 --> 00:40:58,320
I just finished writing the case report.

868
00:40:58,320 --> 00:40:59,960
Can you take a look at it for me?

869
00:41:00,320 --> 00:41:01,400
Who said you could drive my car?

870
00:41:02,119 --> 00:41:03,599
Our car broke down, didn't it?

871
00:41:03,960 --> 00:41:05,679
You should have told me your car broke down.

872
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:07,159
But weren't you sleeping?

873
00:41:07,159 --> 00:41:08,840
You were even snoring, I didn't wake you up.

874
00:41:08,840 --> 00:41:09,960
I'll treat you to a meal another day.

875
00:41:09,960 --> 00:41:11,360
Eat, eat—what meal?

876
00:41:11,360 --> 00:41:12,440
Your mentor has totally led you astray.

877
00:41:12,440 --> 00:41:13,480
Take a look, hurry up and look.

878
00:41:16,719 --> 00:41:18,239
Not bad, the format is all correct.

879
00:41:18,719 --> 00:41:20,679
Your handwriting is even messier than mine.

880
00:41:20,679 --> 00:41:21,679
Practice it later.

881
00:41:21,679 --> 00:41:22,840
As long as it's readable.

882
00:41:26,000 --> 00:41:26,760
Dali

883
00:41:27,239 --> 00:41:28,760
Is that book really that interesting?

884
00:41:28,760 --> 00:41:30,280
I always see you keeping it on the dashboard.

885
00:41:30,280 --> 00:41:31,400
It's a classic.

886
00:41:32,440 --> 00:41:34,679
But the character names are so hard to remember.

887
00:41:34,679 --> 00:41:36,840
Do you know the author's name?

888
00:41:37,039 --> 00:41:38,440
Isn't it Dostoevsky?

889
00:41:38,679 --> 00:41:39,480
The full name.

890
00:41:40,719 --> 00:41:41,840
The full name is

891
00:41:41,840 --> 00:41:45,119
Fyodor Mikhailovich

892
00:41:45,119 --> 00:41:46,360
Dostoevsky.

893
00:41:46,360 --> 00:41:48,360
Such a long name, it's really hard to remember.

894
00:41:48,559 --> 00:41:49,679
And you still read it?

895
00:41:50,239 --> 00:41:50,800
Dali

896
00:41:52,719 --> 00:41:53,960
This gunshot wound

897
00:41:55,280 --> 00:41:55,880
what happened?

898
00:41:56,119 --> 00:41:57,320
No, no, let's not talk about it.

899
00:41:57,400 --> 00:41:58,159
No, come on, tell me about it.

900
00:41:58,159 --> 00:41:59,239
It's all in the past.

901
00:41:59,239 --> 00:42:00,840
What case was it? How did it happen?

902
00:42:00,920 --> 00:42:02,480
We can't keep bringing it up, or I'll keep thinking about it.

903
00:42:02,480 --> 00:42:02,880
Master.

904
00:42:02,880 --> 00:42:04,079
Don't listen to him brag.

905
00:42:04,079 --> 00:42:06,239
He burned that himself with a cigarette.

906
00:42:06,440 --> 00:42:07,480
Old Wei, you're a veteran detective too.

907
00:42:07,480 --> 00:42:09,159
Can you be a bit more responsible with your words?

908
00:42:09,440 --> 00:42:11,000
This is a through-and-through wound.

909
00:42:11,239 --> 00:42:13,119
What kind of cigarette could make such a big scar?

910
00:42:13,159 --> 00:42:13,960
A cigar.

911
00:42:14,239 --> 00:42:15,199
There's another burn on the back.

912
00:42:15,199 --> 00:42:16,280
Who burned it? Me.

913
00:42:16,480 --> 00:42:18,719
Next time, line them up. They're not even straight.

914
00:42:18,719 --> 00:42:19,840
Take a look when you shower.

915
00:42:19,960 --> 00:42:20,559
They're crooked.

916
00:42:20,559 --> 00:42:21,440
One's higher, one's lower.

917
00:42:21,440 --> 00:42:22,480
Crooked.

918
00:42:23,079 --> 00:42:23,880
Uneducated.

919
00:42:23,960 --> 00:42:25,360
I'm not going to argue with you.

920
00:42:25,360 --> 00:42:26,639
I was going to burn four characters too.

921
00:42:26,639 --> 00:42:27,639
But I forgot about it.

922
00:42:27,639 --> 00:42:29,159
I'll burn four characters for you next time, you'll see.

923
00:42:30,400 --> 00:42:31,800
Master, the case report.

924
00:42:33,119 --> 00:42:33,880
You—

925
00:42:34,079 --> 00:42:35,000
Who said the case is closed?

926
00:42:35,719 --> 00:42:36,440
I did.

927
00:42:37,119 --> 00:42:37,800
Where's the knife?

928
00:42:38,440 --> 00:42:39,559
You must have eaten the knife.

929
00:42:41,400 --> 00:42:42,199
Remember this.

930
00:42:42,679 --> 00:42:44,960
A fruit knife with a black handle.

931
00:42:44,960 --> 00:42:46,159
Twenty centimeters long.

932
00:42:47,639 --> 00:42:49,360
Head east from the crime scene, out the east gate.

933
00:42:49,960 --> 00:42:52,440
It's in a trash can, about three hundred meters away.

934
00:42:52,840 --> 00:42:53,559
Go look for it.

935
00:42:55,079 --> 00:42:55,599
Old Wei.

936
00:42:55,599 --> 00:42:56,199
Brother Ma.

937
00:42:56,199 --> 00:42:57,639
Lin Chunmiao's daughter has arrived.

938
00:42:57,639 --> 00:42:58,360
Ziming, hurry up.

939
00:42:58,519 --> 00:42:59,239
Go over there, quickly.
